<p><b>What is KYC in simple words?</b> KYC means "Know Your Customer". It is a process by which banks obtain information about the identity and address of the customers. This process helps to ensure that banks' services are not misused. The KYC procedure is to be completed by the banks while opening accounts and also periodically update the same.</p>
<p><b>What are the new rules for KYC?</b> New rules: - Investors can obtain "KYC-registered" status by completing KYC with other Officially Valid Documents (OVDs) such as Aadhaar, passport, driving licence, or voter ID card. - To obtain "KYC-validated" status, however, PAN and Aadhaar still need to be linked.</p>